<body>

  <h1>AE Backend — Run & Setup Guide</h1>
  <p>This guide explains how to run the American Express Shop & Shipping backend, seed the database, and launch the server in development or production mode.</p>

  <!-- Requirements -->
  <div class="card">
    <h2>Requirements</h2>
    <p>Ensure you have the following installed:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Node.js 18+</li>
      <li>Docker & Docker Compose</li>
      <li>npm (comes with Node.js)</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <!-- Install packages -->
  <div class="card">
    <h2>1. Install Dependencies</h2>
    <pre>npm install</pre>
  </div>

  <!-- Docker instructions -->
  <div class="card">
    <h2>2. Start Postgres using Docker</h2>
    <p>Spin up the database container defined in <strong>docker-compose.yml</strong>:</p>
    <pre>docker compose up -d db</pre>
    <p>This will create:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Database: <strong>ae_db</strong></li>
      <li>User: <strong>ae_user</strong></li>
      <li>Password: <strong>ae_password</strong></li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <!-- Seed database -->
  <div class="card">
    <h2>3. Seed the Database</h2>
    <p>The seed command loads the schema and sample products from <code>db/init.sql</code> using the improved seed script:</p>

    <pre>npm run seed</pre>

    <p>If using Docker for backend, ensure the container can reach Postgres using:</p>
    <pre>postgresql://ae_user:ae_password@db:5432/ae_db</pre>
  </div>

  <!-- Start server -->
  <div class="card">
    <h2>4. Start Backend API</h2>

    <h3>Development Mode</h3>
    <pre>npm run dev</pre>

    <h3>Production Mode</h3>
    <pre>npm start</pre>

    <p>The backend will run on:</p>
    <code>http://localhost:3000</code>
  </div>

  <!-- API info -->
  <div class="card">
    <h2>5. API Endpoints</h2>

    <p>Common endpoints available in <strong>server.js</strong>:</p>

    <ul>
      <li><code>GET /products</code> – List all products</li>
      <li><code>GET /products/:id</code> – Product details</li>
      <li><code>POST /orders</code> – Create new order</li>
      <li><code>GET /orders/:ref</code> – Track an order</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <!-- Troubleshooting -->
  <div class="card">
    <h2>6. Troubleshooting</h2>
    
    <p><strong>Database connection error?</strong></p>
    <pre>Check DATABASE_URL in .env</pre>

    <p><strong>Seed not running?</strong></p>
    <pre>Ensure db/init.sql exists and Docker Postgres is running.</pre>

    <p><strong>Port already in use?</strong></p>
    <pre>Change PORT in .env</pre>
  </div>

  <footer>&copy; 2025 Shoppy Webzy Shop & Shipping — Developer Run Guide</footer>

